    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">188, Strand, W.C.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 13. <hi rend="print">18</hi>78</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Enclosed is proof and copy of the subject you left me reduced on to the block by Photography, and trust you will find it as you desire: with regard to the method of doing them by Photo it comes rather expensive but then you get a scientific accuracy, which is of the utmost value in a work like this still.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I shall be prepared to undertake your work on as reasonable terms as possible for <hi rend="underline">good</hi> work and the <hi rend="underline">average</hi> cost may enable you to employ the means I suggest. Awaiting reply.</p>
<p>I am | Dear Sir | Yours truly | James D Cooper <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The proof has not been found. CD employed Cooper to engrave diagrams, reducing them when necessary, for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5637.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Movement in plants</hi></ref> (see <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 7 ). Cooper had previously made engravings for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1966.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi></ref> and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vols. 19 and 20).</note>
        </div> 
     
    </body>
